Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setFinishFPlanMode(25.10)                            setFinishFPlanMode(25.10)

Name
       setFinishFPlanMode  -  Set the active objects and specifies the channel
       direction for the finishFloorplan command to use whenever  you  perform
       advanced placement-related refinements to a floorplan

Syntax
       setFinishFPlanMode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-abuttedEdgeAsNonRowArea {true|false}]

       [-activeObj     {macro|macroHalo|core|iopad|iocell|fence|hardblkg|soft-
       blkg|partialblkg|routeblkg|row|die}]

       [-direction {<x>|<y>|<xy>}]

       [-drcRegionObj        {macro|macroHalo|hardBlkg|minGap|coreSpacing|non-
       RowArea|row}]

       [-fillOption {channel|boundary}]

       [-override {true|false}]

       Set the active objects and specifies the channel direction for the fin-
       ishFloorplan command to use whenever you perform advanced placement-re-
       lated refinements to a floorplan. Use the getFinishFPlanMode command to
       return  the  current  settings  for the setFinishFPlanMode command. The
       setFinishFPlanMode parameters affects the behavior the  finishFloorplan
       command.

Parameters
       -abuttedEdgeAsNonRowArea {true|false}
              Specifies  whether  the  abutted  edge  of a power domain should
              treated be as nonRowArea.

              * true: The abutted edge of the power domain is treated as  non-
                RowArea  with size 0 by default. The tool creates a DRC region
                around the abutted edge  with  the  finishFloorplan-edgeExtend
                parameter option.

              * false:  The  abutted edge of the power domain is excluded from
                nonRowArea. The tool then does not create a DRC region  around
                the abutted edge with the finishFloorplan-edgeExtend parameter
                option.

              Note:  This  option can only be specified when the -drcRegionObj
              nonRowArea parameter option is also specified.

              For example:

              setFinishFPlanMode -drcRegionObj  nonRowArea  -abuttedEdgeAsNon-
              RowArea {true|false}

              finishFloorplan -drcRegionLayer M1 -edgeExtend {10 10}

              Default: true

              Data_type: bool

       -activeObj {macro|macroHalo|core|iopad|iocell|fence|hardblkg|soft-
       blkg|partialblkg|routeblkg|row|die}
              Specifies  the  active object list. The boundaries of the speci-
              fied active objects are looked at while deciding  where  to  add
              blockages. Non-active objects are treated like they do not exist
              by the finishFloorplan command.

              The active objects can be:

              * core

              * macro

              * macroHalo

              * ioCell

              * ioPad

              * fence

              * hardblkg

              * softblkg

              * partialblkg

              * routeblkg

              * row

              * die

              Default: core macro macroHalo

              Data_type:  enums={macro macroHalo core iopad iocell fence hard-
              blkg softblkg partialblkg routeblkg row die}_list

       -direction {x | y | xy}
              Specifies the direction in which  the  blockage  is  added.  You
              specify one of the following options:

              * x: Fills the channel whose height is less than width.

              * y: Fills the channel whose width is less than height.

              * xy:  Fills every channel whose smallest size (in X or Y direc-
                tion) is within Max Gap range.

              Default: xy

              Data_type: enums={x y xy}

       -drcRegionObj {macro|macroHalo|hardBlkg|minGap|coreSpacing|non-
       RowArea|row}
              Specifies the drc region object  list.  The  boundaries  of  the
              specified  drc region objects are looked at while deciding where
              to add blockages. The drc region objects can be:

              * coreSpacing

              * hardBlkg

              * macro

              * macroHalo

              * minGap

              * nonRowArea

              * row

              Default: macro macroHalo hardBlkg minGap coreSpacing row

              Data_type: enums={macro macroHalo  hardBlkg  minGap  coreSpacing
              nonRowArea row}_list

       -fillOption {channel|boundary}
              Specifies the fill option to be used when blockages are added to
              active objects.

              * channel: Blockages are added to the channel between active ob-
                jects.

                Note: This option does not support die as an active object.

              * boundary:  Blockages  are added around the boundary of the ac-
                tive objects.

                Note: This option only supports macro and die  as  active  ob-
                jects. Only route blockages can be added to the objects bound-
                ary.

                In  other words, finishFloorplan -fillRouteBlockage works with
                setFinishFPlanMode -fillOption boundary.

              Default: channel

              Data_type: enums={channel boundary}_list

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  setFinishFPlanMode  parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command man setFinishFPlanMode.

       -override {true | false}
              Overrides old blockages that overlap with the new blockages.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -reset Restores all parameters  modified  using  setFinishFPlanMode  to
              their  default  settings. The -reset parameter must be the first
              parameter specified. If you specify -reset by itself, the  soft-
              ware  resets  all setFinishFPlanMode parameters to their default
              values. If you specify parameters after -reset, the software re-
              sets only those parameters to their default values.  Any  values
              that  do  not already match the default value and are reset will
              be reported.

Example
              * The following commands specify the region layer name list  for
                creating a region layer for the specified DRC region object:

                setFinishFPlanMode -drcRegionObj macro

                finishFloorplan -drcRegionLayer R1

Related Information
